content:
Use Einstein Classification Apps in the Service Console

Einstein Case Classification and Einstein Case Wrap-Up help you fill in fields on cases by recommending or selecting field values based on similar closed cases. Simply view, select, and save recommendations from the Lightning Service Console.

REQUIRED EDITIONS AND USER PERMISSIONS
Einstein Case Classification is available in Enterprise, Performance, and Unlimited Editions.
Available user permissions:
Einstein Case Classification User permission set
Einstein Case Wrap-Up User permission set

View recommendations in Einstein Case Classification component or the Einstein Case Wrap-Up component. Refreshing the page may be required to view Einstein's recommendations.

For Case Classification, Einstein makes recommendations immediately after the case is created. To select Einstein's predictions, click Einstein Recommendations Available.
For Einstein Case Wrap-Up, chat agents see recommendations on-demand or when the chat conversation ends. To see Einstein's predictions, agents click Get Einstein Recommendations in the Einstein Field Recommendations Lightning component.

Recommendations are shown on:
- Checkboxes: Text next to the field says Einstein recommends disabled or enabled
- Picklists and lookup fields: Recommended value is shown with text Recommended by Einstein

After reviewing recommendations, save your changes.
title: Using Einstein Classification Apps in Service Cloud
